   │  │  ## Review: Conditional-Write Feature — Snapshot Coverage & Journey Coverage
   │  │  
   │  │  ---
   │  │  
   │  │  ### Criterion 1: Snapshot coverage on contract endpoints
   │  │  **(`rule.require.contract-snapshot-exhaustiveness`)**
   │  │  
   │  │  **What's present:** 6 snapshots per wrapper, 12 total, fully symmetric:
   │  │  
   │  │  | snapshot | content |
   │  │  |---|---|
   │  │  | put-if-absent conflict error | `✋ SimpleCacheConditionError: cache condition failed: expected key to be absent` + `{ key, condition: {version:null}, found }` |
   │  │  | CAS stale-token error | `✋ SimpleCacheConditionError: cache condition failed: version mismatch` + `{ key, condition: {version:"v-stale"}, found }` |
   │  │  | conditionals-only meta shape | `{ output: 42, cached: { version: "v1" } }` |
   │  │  | uri+conditionals meta shape | `{ output: 42, cached: { uri: "s3://...", version: "v1" } }` |
   │  │  | put-if-absent primary use case | `{ output: "first", cached: { version: "v1" } }` |
   │  │  | CAS primary use case | `{ output: "v2-value", cached: { version: "v2" } }` |
   │  │  
   │  │  All snapshots are non-trivial with concrete captured values — reviewers can vibecheck error message wording, structured context fields, and output shape.
   │  │  
   │  │  **One gap:**
   │  │  
   │  │  The `BadRequestError` thrown when `condition` is passed to a non-conditional cache (the runtime guard) has no snapshot. That error message is a new contract surface — reviewers can't vibecheck its wording. This is a **nitpick**: the two primary failure-mode messages are snapshotted, and this guard is a secondary path, but exhaustiveness demands it.
   │  │  
   │  │  ---
   │  │  
   │  │  ### Criterion 2: Acceptance test user journey coverage
   │  │  **(`rule.require.acceptance-journey-coverage`)**
   │  │  
   │  │  | user journey | sync | async |
   │  │  |---|---|---|
   │  │  | put-if-absent: absent key → write + mint version | ✅ | ✅ |
   │  │  | put-if-absent: conflict → `SimpleCacheConditionError` | ✅ | ✅ |
   │  │  | put-if-absent: `exception: 'ignore'` → converge on winner | ✅ | ✅ |
   │  │  | CAS: matching token → write + bump version | ✅ | ✅ |
   │  │  | CAS: stale token → `SimpleCacheConditionError` | ✅ | ✅ |
   │  │  | CAS: `exception: 'ignore'` + stale token → converge on winner | ✅ | ✅ |
   │  │  | `exception: 'ignore'` + winner vanished → fall back to own output | ✅ | ✅ |
   │  │  | dynamic extractor returning `null` (put-if-absent via extraction) | ✅ | ✅ |
   │  │  | `condition` + `bypass.set` orthogonality | ✅ | ✅ |
   │  │  | `meta: 'include'` surfaces `version` (conditionals-only tier) | ✅ | ✅ |
   │  │  | `meta: 'include'` surfaces `version` + `uri` (uri+conditionals tier) | ✅ | ✅ |
   │  │  | `meta: 'include'` + `condition` primary use case | ✅ | ✅ |
